OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1784220475
OL,3,CWelsh Government lose supplementary
OL,4,CBudget vote
OL,6,FTalks began after the Plaid Cymru
OL,7,FWelsh Government published its plans
OL,8,Fin its Supplementary Budget, which
OL,9,Fisn't a full budget but rather sets
OL,10,Fout some adjustments in the current
OL,11,Ffinancial year.
OL,13,FIt maintains the overall spending
OL,14,Fplans of the previous Labour Welsh
OL,15,FGovernment but adds #145m towards
OL,16,Fcutting waiting lists in hospitals
OL,17,Falong with #55m towards childcare
OL,18,Ffunding and spending on school
OL,19,Fmaintenance and other capital projects.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/10
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,436,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1784220475
OL,3,CWelsh Government lose supplementary
OL,4,CBudget vote
OL,6,FPlaid Cymru was the largest party
OL,7,Fafter May's Senedd election so forms
OL,8,Fthe Welsh Government, but it doesn't
OL,9,Fhave a majority so needed the support
OL,10,Fof another party in order to win
OL,11,Fvotes, but was unable to do this.
OL,13,FThe main opposition party, Reform UK
OL,14,FWales, ruled out backing it saying
OL,15,Fthat it failed to put Wales first, and
OL,16,F"takes money from children with
OL,17,Fadditional learning needs while
OL,18,Fcontinuing to send taxpayers' money
OL,19,Fabroad." Welsh Conservatives also said
OL,20,Fthey wouldn't back it.
OL,26,@xD@AOU{D@HO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/10
