OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1784220475
OL,3,CWelsh Government lose supplementary
OL,4,CBudget vote
OL,6,FToday both have stated to ITV Cymru
OL,7,FWales that no formal talks or
OL,8,Fapproaches have been made and they
OL,9,Freiterated their decision to vote
OL,10,Fagainst the supplementary budget.
OL,12,FTalks have been taking place with
OL,13,FWelsh Labour, but they haven't gone
OL,14,Fsmoothly. Labour has made spending on
OL,15,FAdditional Learning Needs (ALN) in
OL,16,Fschool the focus of negotiations.
OL,18,FAs a result of spending in England
OL,19,Frelated to ALN, the Welsh Government
OL,20,Freceived a #327m boost to its budget
OL,21,Ffor this financial year.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/10
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
