OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1784220475
OL,3,CWelsh Government lose supplementary
OL,4,CBudget vote
OL,6,FThe Welsh Government offered first
OL,7,F#80m over two years, then #120m over
OL,8,Fthree years. Labour has now rejected
OL,9,Fthat offer and urged the Finance
OL,10,FMinister to withdraw the supplementary
OL,11,Fbudget.
OL,13,FLabour's interim leader, Ken Skates,
OL,14,Ftold ITV Cymru Wales that, "At a very
OL,15,Flate stage, it's become apparent that
OL,16,Fthe Welsh Government is now in dispute
OL,17,Fwith teaching unions over pay and over
OL,18,Fa lack of support for Additional
OL,19,FLearning Needs that has to be resolved.
OL,26,@vD@\OU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/10
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,436,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1784220475
OL,3,CWelsh Government lose supplementary
OL,4,CBudget vote
OL,6,F"They're now negotiating on multiple
OL,7,Ffronts, and it's been, quite frankly,
OL,8,Fa chaotic process of negotiations. And
OL,9,Fso there is no other option, in my
OL,10,Fview, for the government other than to
OL,11,Fwithdraw this supplementary budget."
OL,13,FIf there's no withdrawal, he said,
OL,14,FLabour MSs will vote against tonight,
OL,15,Fmeaning that the Welsh Government is
OL,16,Fcertain to be defeated.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@dO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/10
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
